Rachael Saleigh, Chalo's character, from the webcomic "Las Lindas". Works best on 1.0. Training done on NAI.

items.name: Aardman Animations Style (LORA)
items.description:
Hey, all, I'm back with another LoRA, and it's based on the stop-motion claymation style of Aardman Animations! I really enjoy their exaggerated cartoonish style of clay models from their works such as Chicken Run, Shaun The Sheep (one of my childhood favorites), Wallace & Gromit, and so much more! Trained this on over 77 images from their shows and movies.

Recommended settings:

LoRA weight: ~0.6-0.9 (I would highly recommend to put ~0.6-0.8 for the most accurate results if you're doing hires. fix)

If you're doing hires. fix, I suggest the denoising range of ~0.55-0.7

CFG scale: 5-7

Checkpoints: I recommend Deliberate since it's the one that I tested out the most, and provided accurate results (but you can experiment with others as well)

Samplers: Euler a, DPM++ 2M Karras, or DPM++ SDE Karras

Make sure you add "aardman style" to enable the effect on your prompt!

Negative prompt that works well:

paintings, sketches, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), dot, mole, lowers, normal quality, monochrome, grayscale, lowers, text, error, cropped, worst quality, low quality, jpeg artifacts, ugly, duplicate, morbid, mutilated, out of frame, extra fingers, mutated hands, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn face, mutation, deformed, blurry, dehydrated, bad anatomy, bad proportions, extra limbs, cloned face, disfigured, gross proportions, malformed limbs, missing arms, missing legs, extra arms, extra legs, fused fingers, too many fingers, long neck, username, watermark, signature, less than five fingers, EasyNegative, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

Suggestions and feedback are always welcome!

I hope you enjoy my LoRA!

items.name: SWEETAI | OC Claire Addams | V1
items.description:
Some fun concept i had in mind, the first time i saw a goth girl was when i was a kid in the 90's (1991 version)

and you can bet your ass i goth the goth (lol) fetish right there


and why not mix the most beautiful girl in the world (Claire Redfield, RE2R) with Wednesday Addams (OG One, outfit and hair only, albeit more...skimpy), well? thats exactly what i did!


also remember, my work will be ALWAYS FREE and continuously improving, so all i ask is for a donation, if i don't get enough support i will stop providing free models eventually


oh and yeah i learned captioning (i had the click, finally i can sleep now!), i mastered SFM, i mastered Blender, and i will fucking master AI, learning alone with frustration increases one will power instead of relying on others

all is missing is NMKD fixing inpainting on 1.12 (it worked on NON-INPAINTING models on 1.9.1!!!) and adding ControlNet (gotta make these horny poses!) then i'm set, i don't give a fuck about

sdxl because it looks plastic and i read/heard that the training speed is abyssmal even on a 3090, that's absolutely not for me, and it is taking a long time to mature


note: there is some fuckery going on with her hair as the hair i got from Daz (a 2million vert hair, what.the.fuck) had a major split in the middle, so you might get some heavy baldness on that split in the middle.

note2: i will always include example prompts so you don't have to smash your head against the wall trying to guess then

note3: if you aren't getting enough braids make sure to include it on your prompts to give the AI a hand.

note4: people say you don't have control over AI and AI does all the job, let me change that, this is me doing already doing 60% of the lifting (i can do every single of these renders in blender, but slower ofc, AI is just a tool to speed an artist workflow not to replace the artist), we are like brothers now, working together for a world free of paywalls.

=====

Trigger Words are claire for face, and addams for outfit

Trained on 209 images (16 which are rendered at 4K 512 samples for close ups)

Trained on resolution 768x768

Tested on 1024x1024 resolution (high-res fix enabled)

Trained on BASE 1.5

CFG 7

Steps 40

Tested on CyberRealistic 3.2 only

Trained using NMKD GUI at a Learning Rate of 0.00070 and 740 Training Steps ( thank you https://talkai.info/)

Weight used on previews: 1

====

DISCLAIMER

I did not include ANY image of Jordan McEwen in this dataset, they are ALL exclusively rendered using Blender at a resolution of 1920x1920 using the in-game character extracted directly from the game (Resident Evil 2 Remake)

#========================#

TOOLS USED TO CREATE MY MODELS

#========================#

Blender 3.5 (Custom Dataset Creation for Characters)

DaVinci Resolve (Improve Dataset Quality using Various Techniques)

NMKD Gui (LyCORIS Model Training and Debugging, Image Previews)

My work flow was to generate in automatic1111 with the refiner extension at 15% steps.

The Lora had some trouble generating a clear face at distance, this may be fixed using inpainting.

You can use triggers like fox mask, rogue, black hood, glowing eyes, etc.

Let me know if you like it or if there are any changes I can work on!

items.name: Gustav Klimt SDXL 1.0 art style lora
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Gustav Klimt art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Gustav Klimt is an Austrian Symbolist painter and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 and is able to produce higher details than if you were to simply put his name into your prompt. You can however add "in the style of Gustav Klimt" to your prompt along with the LoRa and trigger for a slightly different effect.

This is a LoRa where you really want to experiment with different aspect ratios especially long and thin ones as a lot of his paintings were done that way.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to adjust it depending on the complexity of your prompt. I've used it as high as 1.5. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 7 works well for this art style.

The main trigger is kl1m which you can use on its own and you can use these additional tags on top of the main trigger to provide variation. When using these you may have to adjust LoRa weight periodically. The best way to use them would be to put them in a wildcard and add one or two to your prompt or to play around with each one individually and see which ones you like best. They are meant to provide variety on top of the main trigger tag:

pr3g
d4ff
tt3r
ch0i
v1rg
3st
k1s5
gd3y
gf5h
wsnk
fnnn
snfl
hp03
whl3
mzrt
3mil
phse

Since the dataset was acquired from various sources across the web I do not have all of the names of each painting those trigger words were trained on. They are obfuscated in 1337 speak so that the SDXL AI does not misinterpret them. Until dreambooth gets implemented into kohya custom captioning wont work the way it did in SD1.5 so this is the best I can do for now.


Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

Samples at 1 strength+highres.

I wanted to make a cool all 4 characters in 1 pic, but my latent couple died every time I tried to change from the defaults (I also manually edited over 100 .txt in the dataset files only for that) :(

Trigger Words:

immatsuri for Matsuri

immiu for Miu

imchika for Chika

imana for Ana

Some details and rarely colors can bleed, using the negative prompt can easily fix that, but not if you're using latent couple. Example: if you're getting Matsuri glasses on other characters, just add glasses to the negative.

I didn't feel like I need to add other characteristics besides the trigger word to get a character, but you can also try adding if the model you're using struggles to get certain concept.

You can support me here

Enjoy :D
